cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.OS, cs.CR

This paper discusses a consistency model for geo-replicated data stores, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper specifically focuses on a key-value store developed for high availability and performance requirements, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of Hybrid Logical Clocks, which are commonly used in operating systems (cs.OS) and the paper addresses the issue of slowdown cascades, which is a concern in the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
